'''Basaa''' (also spelled ''Bassa, Basa, Bissa''), or '''Mbene''', is a [[Bantu languages|Bantu language]] spoken in [[Cameroon]] by the [[Bassa people (Cameroon)|Basaa people]]. It is spoken by about 300,000 people in [[Centre Province, Cameroon|Centre]] and [[Littoral Province, Cameroon|Littoral]] regions.

Maho (2009) lists [[Kogo language|North and South Kogo]] as dialects.

