* {{IPA|/m, p, b/}} are [[Bilabial consonant|bilabial]], whereas {{IPA|/f, v/}} are [[Labiodental consonant|labiodental]].
* {{IPA|/p, b, t, d, k, g/}} are singly articulated plosives, {{IPA|/t͡ʃ, d͡ʒ/}} are affricates (stops with a strong fricative release), whereas {{IPA|/k͡p, ɡ͡b/}} are [[Doubly articulated consonant|doubly articulated]] plosives.
* {{IPA|/l/}} varies between a lateral approximant {{IPAblink|l}} and a central trill {{IPAblink|r}}.{{citation needed|date=August 2015}}
* {{IPA|/j/}} has a fricative allophone {{IPAblink|ʒ}}.{{citation needed|date=August 2015}}

===Vowels===
[[File:Dangme vowel chart.svg|thumb|250px|[[Monophthong]]s of Dangme, from {{Harvcoltxt|Kropp Dakubu|1987|p=15}}]]
Adangme has 7 oral vowels and 5 nasal vowels.{{sfnp|Kropp Dakubu|1987|p=15}}

