{{primary sources|date=August 2018}} {{confused|sports club}}
[[File:Youth-soccer-indiana.jpg|thumb|two teams, yellow and green, compete in an [[association football]] match]]
A '''sports team''' is a group of individuals who play [[sport|sports]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thefreedictionary.com/Sports+team|title=Sports team|work=TheFreeDictionary.com|access-date=2018-08-30}}</ref>, usually [[team sport|team sports]], on the same [[team]]. Historically, sports teams and the people who play sports have been [[amateur sports|amateurs]]. However, by the 20th century, some sports teams and their associated leagues became extremely valuable with net worth in the millions. The [[Dallas Cowboys]] are rated by [[Forbes]] as the world's [[Forbes' list of the most valuable sports teams|most valuable sports team]] at $4.2 billion USD.<ref>{{cite web | first=Kurt |last=Badenhausen |title=The World's 50 Most Valuable Sports Teams 2017 | journal=Forbes |date=July 5, 2018 | url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/kurtbadenhausen/2017/07/12/full-list-the-worlds-50-most-valuable-sports-teams-2017 | accessdate=July 5, 2018}}</ref> Some [[individual sport|individual sports]] have modified rules that allow them to be played by teams.
Team identities can be formed from a number of sources, most often a type of geographic location, e.g., the [[Dallas Cowboys]] are named after [[Dallas]], Texas, US.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dallascowboys.com/|title=Dallas Cowboys {{!}} Official Site of the Dallas Cowboys|website=www.dallascowboys.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-08-30}}</ref> Some teams can also be named after an institution, such as the [[Alabama Crimson Tide]], which are supported by and named after the [[University of Alabama]], or the [[Yomiuri Giants]], who are named after the [[Yomiuri Group]], a Japanese media conglomerate.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://info.yomiuri.co.jp/english/about.html|title=About the Yomiuri Shimbun Group ： Corporate Profile of The Yomiuri Shimbun|website=Corporate Profile of The Yomiuri Shimbun|language=ja|access-date=2018-08-30}}</ref>
