{{Infobox language |name=Äiwoo |altname=Reef |states=[[Solomon Islands]] |region=[[Santa Cruz Islands]], eastern Solomons, [[Temotu Province]]. |speakers=8,400 |date = 1999 |ref=e18 |coordinates = {{coord|10|13|S|166|12|E|type:landmark|display=inline}} |familycolor=Austronesian |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]] |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] |fam4=[[Temotu languages|Temotu]] ? |fam5=[[Reefs – Santa Cruz languages|Reefs – Santa Cruz]] |iso3=nfl |script=[[Latin script|Latin]] |glotto=ayiw1239 |glottorefname=Ayiwo }}
'''Äiwoo''' is a [[language]] spoken in the [[Reef Islands]] and [[Nendö]] ([[Santa Cruz Islands]]), both part of the [[Temotu Province]] in the Eastern [[Solomon Islands]].
==Classification== Äiwoo belongs to the [[Reef Islands – Santa Cruz languages]], a member of the [[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]] subgroup of the [[Austronesian languages|Austronesian]] language family.
==Distribution== Äiwoo is the largest of the ''Reef Islands – Santa Cruz'' languages, with approximately 8000 native speakers. Most speakers live in the [[Ngawa (Solomon Islands)|Ngawa]] district and the island [[Ngäsinue]] in the Reef Islands; others live in some villages of [[Vanikoro]] or of [[Nendo Island|Nendö]], like [[Kala Bay]]. Finally, some communities have recently been established in the capital [[Honiara]] – notably in the ''White River'' district.
== External links == * [[Paradisec]] has a collection of [http://catalog.paradisec.org.au/collections/AN1 Äiwoo recordings]. They also have a collection of [[Stephen Wurm]]'s recordings, which [http://catalog.paradisec.org.au/collections/SAW2 includes some Äiwoo material.]
